    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::ec_transition_outside_transaction": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::ec_transition_outside_transaction",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "tryTransitionToVerified is called after the transaction completes in vote routes; a transition failure returns 500 even though the vote was committed",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "app/api/vote/route.ts",
          "app/api/restaurant-vote/route.ts",
          "lib/rules.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "app/api/vote/route.ts: prisma.$transaction (lines 60-80) commits the vote and recommendation update; tryTransitionToVerified (line 83) is called after the transaction closes",
          "app/api/restaurant-vote/route.ts: same pattern \u2014 transaction on lines 60-80, tryTransitionToVerified on line 83",
          "lib/rules.ts tryTransitionToVerified does a prisma.restaurant.findUnique and prisma.restaurant.update \u2014 if either throws (DB transient error), the error propagates to the route handler's outer try/catch which returns 500",
          "The vote has already been durably written; returning 500 misleads the client into believing the vote failed and causes it to revert the optimistic update incorrectly"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Wrap the tryTransitionToVerified call in its own try/catch in each route handler, and swallow or log the error without returning a non-2xx status. The transition is a best-effort side effect \u2014 the vote is the primary outcome. Example: `try { await tryTransitionToVerified(id); } catch (e) { console.error('transition failed', e); }` placed after the transaction.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "804a5927"
      },
      "status": "fixed",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
      "first_seen": "2026-04-02T12:33:10+00:00",
