    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::ec_loadmore_unhandled_fetch_error": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::ec_loadmore_unhandled_fetch_error",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "LoadMoreButton.tsx loadMore() has no catch clause; a fetch failure produces no user feedback and leaves hasMore in an inconsistent state",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "components/LoadMoreButton.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "components/LoadMoreButton.tsx loadMore() (lines 165-190): try/finally with no catch block",
          "If fetch() throws (network error) or res.json() throws, the finally block runs setLoading(false) but setHasMore, setGroups, setOffset are not updated \u2014 the component shows the 'More' button with no indication of failure",
          "Sibling pattern in RestaurantFeedbackButton.tsx has a catch block that reverts the optimistic update \u2014 the LoadMore case is inconsistent with that pattern"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Add a catch block to loadMore() that sets an error state or at minimum sets setHasMore(false) to prevent infinite retry attempts. A minimal fix: `catch { setHasMore(false); }` prevents the spinner getting stuck while keeping the change small.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "48b197a5"
      },
