      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "@prisma/client is in devDependencies rather than dependencies, risking runtime breakage when devDeps are pruned during deployment",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "dependency_health",
        "related_files": [
          "package.json"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "package.json devDependencies: `\"@prisma/client\": \"^6.19.2\"` \u2014 the generated client is imported at runtime by lib/db.ts which has 9 importers across the application",
          "Prisma's own documentation places @prisma/client in `dependencies`, not `devDependencies`, because the generated client is required at runtime",
          "The postinstall script runs `prisma generate` which generates the client, but if devDependencies are pruned post-build (common in Docker/CI), the generated client artifacts may still be present while the package resolution chain breaks"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Move `@prisma/client` from `devDependencies` to `dependencies` in package.json. Keep the `prisma` CLI in devDependencies (it is build-time only). This matches the official Prisma setup guide and prevents silent breakage in prune-devdeps deployment environments.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "11f64f70"
      },
      "status": "fixed",
      "note": "Moved @prisma/client from devDependencies to dependencies in package.json. The prisma CLI remains in devDependencies (build-time only).",
