          "triggerScrape is called unconditionally when `grouped.length < 3` \u2014 this condition will be true for every request during the initial data-building phase for a city/query combination",
          "triggerScrape uses fire-and-forget fetch with `.catch(() => undefined)` \u2014 there is no way to know if a scrape is already in progress for this city+query pair",
          "Multiple concurrent users searching for the same low-result query will each trigger independent scrape jobs, fanning out to Reddit and Google Places APIs simultaneously"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Add a short-lived in-memory Set (or Redis key if available) keyed on `${city}:${query}` that is checked before triggering and cleared after the scrape completes (or after a TTL). Alternatively, accept the duplicate scrape risk but add a minimum interval guard (e.g., skip if a scrape was triggered within the last 60 seconds for this key).",
