    "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::redundant_nullish_coalesce_typed_props": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::redundant_nullish_coalesce_typed_props",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "initialUpvotes and initialDownvotes typed as number but guarded with ?? 0 in useState",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "logic_clarity",
        "related_files": [
          "components/RestaurantFeedbackButton.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "RestaurantFeedbackButton.tsx line 21: `const [upvotes, setUpvotes] = useState(initialUpvotes ?? 0)` \u2014 initialUpvotes is typed as `number` in the interface (line 7), so `?? 0` can never trigger.",
          "RestaurantFeedbackButton.tsx line 22: same pattern for `initialDownvotes ?? 0`.",
          "The `?? 0` suggests the author was uncertain whether the prop could be undefined, which conflicts with the non-optional type annotation."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Remove the `?? 0` fallbacks: `useState(initialUpvotes)` and `useState(initialDownvotes)`. If the upstream callers might pass undefined, update the prop type to `number | undefined` to make the optionality explicit.",
