          "components/SearchPoller.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "app/api/search/route.ts: `if (grouped.length < 3) { triggerScrape(...) }` \u2014 fires a fire-and-forget scrape from the server when results are sparse",
          "components/SearchPoller.tsx: unconditionally calls `fetch('/api/scrape', { method: 'POST', ... })` on mount for every search, regardless of existing result count",
          "Both triggers use the same /api/scrape endpoint with the same city and query parameters \u2014 two scrape jobs will run concurrently for every search with fewer than 3 results"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Remove the triggerScrape() call from app/api/search/route.ts and let SearchPoller be the single authority for initiating scrapes. Alternatively, remove the client-side scrape from SearchPoller and rely entirely on the server-side trigger \u2014 but the server trigger is fire-and-forget and cannot update the client, so SearchPoller's polling model is the better owner.",
