      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::ec_openrouter_silent_empty",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "getRedditRecommendations returns [] on API failure, making network errors indistinguishable from genuine no-results",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "lib/openrouter.ts",
          "app/api/scrape/route.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "lib/openrouter.ts getRedditRecommendations(): catch block returns []",
          "Also returns [] when response is not ok (non-200 status)",
          "Also returns [] when API key is missing",
          "app/api/scrape/route.ts fetchWithFallback(): treats llmRecs.length === 0 as FAILED \u2014 so a transient network error to OpenRouter permanently marks the scrape as FAILED rather than retryable"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Distinguish the three empty cases: (1) no API key \u2014 return [] is appropriate (graceful skip); (2) API error \u2014 throw or return a typed Result so the caller can decide to retry or log; (3) empty results \u2014 return []. This allows the scrape pipeline to treat network failures differently from genuine empty recommendations.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "5be06e3f"
