          "Each string field check follows the exact same 4-line pattern: check === null || === undefined, throw; check === '', throw. This pattern is repeated ~25 times across validateParsedQuery, validateRedditPost, validateExtractedRestaurant, validatePlaceDetails, validateRestaurantInput, validateCommunityRecommendationInput, validateRestaurantVoteInput, validateVoteInput.",
          "validateRedditPost uses a field list loop (REDDIT_POST_STRING_FIELDS) for string fields \u2014 demonstrating awareness of the pattern \u2014 but the other 7 validators duplicate the pattern inline."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extend the field-loop pattern used in validateRedditPost to a shared helper: `function requireString(obj: Record<string, unknown>, field: string, context: string): void`. Each validator can then call requireString(obj, 'name', 'Restaurant') instead of repeating the two-branch check inline. This reduces the 274-line file by roughly 40% while keeping each validator's intent clear. The helper stays private within validate.ts.",
