          "Lines 27-30: guard checks direction !== 'up' && direction !== 'down' \u2014 this narrows the runtime value but TypeScript still sees direction as `string | undefined` after the guard",
          "Line 56: `const voteDirection = direction === 'up' ? VoteDirection.up : VoteDirection.down` \u2014 ternary on an unnarrowed string; if somehow direction is undefined here (defensive guard was satisfied by other means), this would silently produce VoteDirection.down"
