      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::trytransitiontoverified_called_after_tra",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "tryTransitionToVerified called after transaction commits in both vote routes; transition failure returns 500 on a committed vote",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "app/api/vote/route.ts",
          "app/api/restaurant-vote/route.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "In app/api/vote/route.ts (line 83) and app/api/restaurant-vote/route.ts (line 83), tryTransitionToVerified is called after the prisma.$transaction block completes. If this call throws (e.g. a DB error on the status update), the handler returns a 500 to the client even though the vote record and upvotes/downvotes increment were already committed. The client receives an error but the vote was recorded."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either include the status transition inside the transaction, or catch errors from tryTransitionToVerified separately and return a success response with a warning rather than a 500.",
