      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::getredditrecommendations_returns_on_a",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "getRedditRecommendations returns [] on API failure, making network errors indistinguishable from genuine no-results",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "lib/openrouter.ts",
          "app/api/scrape/route.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "lib/openrouter.ts getRedditRecommendations returns [] on: missing API key (line 79), non-OK HTTP response (line 113-115), parse exception (line 135-138), and malformed response shape (line 127). The caller in app/api/scrape/route.ts checks llmRecs.length === 0 to decide if the fallback found nothing, then advances the state machine to FAILED. A transient API outage produces the same FAILED outcome as a genuine no-results response."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Return a discriminated result from getRedditRecommendations (e.g. { ok: true, results } | { ok: false, error }) or throw on API failure. The caller can then distinguish error paths from genuine empty results.",
