      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Background scrape trigger in /api/search fires on every low-result request with no rate-limiting or in-flight deduplication guard",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "mid_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "app/api/search/route.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "app/api/search/route.ts lines 9-19 and 52-54: triggerScrape is called when grouped.length < 3, unconditionally on every matching request",
          "triggerScrape uses fire-and-forget fetch with .catch(() => undefined) \u2014 no record of in-flight scrapes, no cooldown, no deduplication by (city, query)",
          "A burst of requests for the same low-result query (e.g. concurrent users) would trigger multiple parallel scrape jobs against the same city+query"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Add a simple server-side deduplication guard: keep an in-memory Set of active scrape keys (city+query hash) and skip triggerScrape if a key is already present, removing it after the scrape completes or times out. This is a one-file change that prevents redundant pipeline invocations without requiring external infrastructure.",
