      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "GET /api/search and GET /api/search-more return structurally incompatible response envelopes for the same resource type",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "app/api/search-more/route.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "GET /api/search returns { city, terms, results: RestaurantGroup[], count: number }. GET /api/search-more returns { results: RestaurantGroup[], hasMore: boolean, nextOffset: number }. Both serve the same resource (grouped restaurants) but use different envelope keys. The /search endpoint echoes city and terms; /search-more does not. The pagination-specific keys (hasMore, nextOffset) in /search-more vs count in /search mean callers must implement different logic to determine result completeness. Note: the previous issue about /search-more returning ungrouped data appears resolved \u2014 grouping now happens server-side."
