          "Lines 144-148: `const internalToken = process.env.INTERNAL_API_TOKEN; if (internalToken) { if (request.headers.get('x-internal-token') !== internalToken) { return 403 } }`. When INTERNAL_API_TOKEN is absent from the environment, the outer `if (internalToken)` evaluates to false and the entire auth check is skipped. Any caller can POST to /api/scrape, triggering Reddit API calls, Google Places API calls, and DB writes without restriction. There is no fallback rejection when the env var is absent. The comment 'Omitting INTERNAL_API_TOKEN is only safe in local dev' is correct but does not enforce the constraint."
        ],
        "suggestion": "See summary for recommended fix.",
