    "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::fetch_with_fallback_dead_state_param": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::fetch_with_fallback_dead_state_param",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "fetchWithFallback in app/api/scrape/route.ts receives a 'state' parameter that is never read and returns a stale value",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "logic_clarity",
        "related_files": [
          "app/api/scrape/route.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Line 22: async function fetchWithFallback(city, query, state: ScrapeState, advance) \u2014 state parameter declared",
          "Inside the function, 'state' is never read \u2014 all state transitions go through advance() callback which closes over the outer state variable in POST scope",
          "Line 46: return { results, state, empty: false, terms } \u2014 returns the parameter value unchanged, which is always 'PENDING' because it was captured by value at call time",
          "The advance() callbacks inside the function mutate the outer scope's state, not this parameter"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Remove the state parameter from fetchWithFallback. Remove 'state' from its return type. The caller already owns the authoritative state variable via the advance closure.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "65a764d3"
      },
      "status": "open",
